<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10495] Invalid newlines generated by XmlTemplateEngine</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10495</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In our recent project, we found a formatting bug of &lt;tt&gt;XmlTemplateEngine&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We expect the following test pass:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        XmlTemplateEngine xmlTemplateEngine = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; XmlTemplateEngine();
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; xmlScript = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;lt;person&amp;gt;\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                         + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;  &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;Daniel&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                         + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;lt;/person&amp;gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;;
        Template template = xmlTemplateEngine.createTemplate(xmlScript);
        assertTrue(template.make().toString().contains(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;lt;name&amp;gt;Daniel&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// no newlines&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But we get(see the newlines around &lt;tt&gt;Daniel&lt;/tt&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;person&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;name&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    Daniel
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/person&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a result, we will get additional newlines if we parse the generated xml and fetch the text of &lt;tt&gt;name&lt;/tt&gt; element.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
